# Navigation Refactor Walkthrough

I have successfully completed the navigation refactor for InternLink. By moving from a single giant stack navigator to modular nested navigators, the application is now much easier to maintain, will run more smoothly, and sets a great foundation for handling authenticated user states.

## What changed

### 1. Extracted Navigation Logic
I created a new directory `src/navigation` and broke down the massive list of screens in `App.tsx` into 8 focused navigators:
- **[AuthNavigator.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Priscilla%20Anokye/InternLink/src/navigation/AuthNavigator.tsx)**: Handles Splash, Login, SignUp, and password recovery screens.
- **[StudentOnboardingNavigator.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Priscilla%20Anokye/InternLink/src/navigation/StudentOnboardingNavigator.tsx)**: Manages the student-specific onboarding flow (Academic Info, Skills, etc).
- **[UniversityOnboardingNavigator.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Priscilla%20Anokye/InternLink/src/navigation/UniversityOnboardingNavigator.tsx)**
- **[CompanyOnboardingNavigator.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Priscilla%20Anokye/InternLink/src/navigation/CompanyOnboardingNavigator.tsx)**
- **[StudentAppNavigator.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Priscilla%20Anokye/InternLink/src/navigation/StudentAppNavigator.tsx)**: The main dashboard and experience for a logged-in student.
- **[UniversityAppNavigator.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Priscilla%20Anokye/InternLink/src/navigation/UniversityAppNavigator.tsx)**: The dashboard for universities.
- **[SettingsNavigator.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Priscilla%20Anokye/InternLink/src/navigation/SettingsNavigator.tsx)**: Houses all the detailed settings and preference pages.
- **[SystemStateNavigator.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Priscilla%20Anokye/InternLink/src/navigation/SystemStateNavigator.tsx)**: Stores the reusable system pages (No Connection, Loading, etc).

### 2. Streamlined App.tsx
Your [App.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Priscilla%20Anokye/InternLink/App.tsx) has been dramatically reduced in size. Instead of registering 40+ individual screens, it now only mounts the 8 top-level navigators. The initial route is set to the `AuthNavigator`, so the app will naturally start at the Splash screen just like before.

### 3. Updated Routing
I updated the [OnboardingRouter.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Priscilla%20Anokye/InternLink/app/OnboardingRouter.tsx) to point to the new Navigator module names (e.g., `StudentOnboarding` instead of `AcademicInfo`), so that user flows continue seamlessly into the correct set of screens.

